# Personal OS Agent Stack

Claude is the planning layer. Cursor Composer and Codex are execution layers.

## Before Work

- Read `AGENTS.md`.
- Read `handoff.md`, `active-backlog.md`, and `memory/MEMORY.md`.
- If `.context/builds/{feature}/prd.md` or `slices.md` exists, implement from it.
- Do not reopen product strategy unless the plan is unsafe, contradictory, or impossible.

## Execution Rules

- Keep patches small.
- Reuse existing code first.
- Fill the matching lane in `docs/agent-task-templates.md` before non-trivial edits.
- Use `docs/qa/*` when the change touches a matching product surface.
- Run `scripts/detect-change-risk` after edits.
- Run `scripts/verify-before-ship` before commit, push, PR, merge, or deploy.
- Update slice boards through `scripts/slice-board.py`.

## Approval Rules

- Production deploy requires the exact phrase `approved to deploy production`.
- Production DB mutation requires the exact phrase `approved for production DB mutation`.
- Short approvals apply only to the last explicitly named action.
